# üî§ Cybersecurity Acronyms Guide

## üìö Introduction
Welcome to the comprehensive guide to cybersecurity acronyms! This resource helps you understand the common terminology used in the cybersecurity field. Whether you're a student, professional, or enthusiast, this guide will help you navigate the complex world of cybersecurity terminology.

## üîí Access & Authentication
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| ACL | Access Control List | List defining permissions for accessing resources |
| IAM | Identity and Access Management | Controls user access and identity verification |
| MFA | Multi-Factor Authentication | Requires multiple forms of verification to access systems |
| SSO | Single Sign-On | Allows users to access multiple applications with one login |
| U2F | Universal 2nd Factor | Standard for two-factor authentication using hardware tokens |
| PAM | Privileged Access Management | Controls and monitors access to critical systems and data |
| DAC | Discretionary Access Control | Access control where owners decide permissions |
| MAC | Mandatory Access Control | Access control based on policies and classifications |

## üõ°Ô∏è Security Systems & Tools
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| IDS | Intrusion Detection System | Monitors network traffic for suspicious activity |
| IPS | Intrusion Prevention System | Blocks or prevents detected threats from causing harm |
| SIEM | Security Information and Event Management | System for managing and analyzing security alerts |
| WAF | Web Application Firewall | Protects web applications by filtering and monitoring HTTP traffic |
| EDR | Endpoint Detection and Response | Monitors and responds to threats on end-user devices |
| DLP | Data Loss Prevention | Measures to protect data from being lost or stolen |
| FIM | File Integrity Monitoring | Monitors files to detect unauthorized changes |
| HIDS | Host-based Intrusion Detection System | Monitors individual hosts for malicious activity |
| NIDS | Network-based Intrusion Detection System | Monitors network traffic for malicious activity |
| HIPS | Host-based Intrusion Prevention System | Prevents malicious activity on individual hosts |

## üåê Network & Infrastructure
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| VPN | Virtual Private Network | Securely connects to a remote network over the internet |
| SSL | Secure Sockets Layer | Encrypts data transmitted over the internet |
| TLS | Transport Layer Security | Updated version of SSL for secure internet communication |
| DMZ | Demilitarized Zone | Network segment that separates external and internal networks |
| VLAN | Virtual Local Area Network | Subnetwork within a network that isolates traffic |
| NAC | Network Access Control | Controls access to a network based on policies |
| BPF | Berkeley Packet Filter | Framework for packet filtering and network analysis |
| L2TP | Layer 2 Tunneling Protocol | Protocol for creating secure VPN connections |

## ‚òÅÔ∏è Cloud Security
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| SaaS | Software as a Service | Software delivery model where applications are hosted by a third-party provider |
| IaaS | Infrastructure as a Service | Cloud computing model that provides virtualized computing resources |
| PaaS | Platform as a Service | Cloud computing model that provides a platform for application development |
| CSPM | Cloud Security Posture Management | Tools for managing and securing cloud infrastructure |

## üè¢ Organization & Management
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| SOC | Security Operations Center | Centralized unit monitoring and managing security events |
| GRC | Governance, Risk, and Compliance | Framework for managing organizational governance, risks, and compliance |
| CISO | Chief Information Security Officer | Senior executive responsible for organization's information security |
| MSSP | Managed Security Service Provider | Company providing outsourced security services |
| BIA | Business Impact Analysis | Evaluates the effects of disruptions on business operations |
| RPO | Recovery Point Objective | Maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time |
| RTO | Recovery Time Objective | Maximum acceptable amount of time to restore a system |

## üêû Threats & Vulnerabilities
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| DDoS | Distributed Denial of Service | Attack that floods a network or service to disrupt availability |
| RAT | Remote Access Trojan | Malware that provides remote control over an infected device |
| XSS | Cross-Site Scripting | Vulnerability allowing attackers to inject scripts into webpages |
| SQLi | SQL Injection | Attack that exploits vulnerabilities in a web application's database query |
| PUP | Potentially Unwanted Program | Software that may be unwanted or harmful |
| CVE | Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures | List of publicly known security vulnerabilities |
| TTP | Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures | Methods used by attackers to achieve their objectives |

## üîê Cryptography & Authentication
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| PKI | Public Key Infrastructure | Framework for managing digital certificates and encryption keys |
| GPG | GNU Privacy Guard | Encryption tool for securing communications and data |
| HMAC | Hash-based Message Authentication Code | Uses a hash function and a secret key to verify data integrity |

## üìä Analytics & Monitoring
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| UEBA | User and Entity Behavior Analytics | Analyzes behavior to detect anomalies and potential threats |

## üèõÔ∏è Standards & Frameworks
| Acronym | Full Term | Definition |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| NIST | National Institute of Standards and Technology | U.S. agency that develops standards for technology and security |

